5|$|Jains believe Mahavira {{attained}} omniscience {{at the age}} of 42, under a Sala tree on {{the banks}} of River Rijupalika near Jrimbhikagrama. He preached, then died {{at the age of}} 72. The Jain Śvētāmbara tradition <b>believes</b> <b>his</b> death occurred in 527 BC, while the Digambara Jain tradition believes this happened in 510 BC. His jiva (soul) is believed in all Jain traditions to be in Siddhashila (abode of the liberated souls).|$|E
